<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="553" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,871,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Description.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[359,460,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1819,1842]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,204,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[156,1431,195,1795]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Bombyciella spp., adults. 1. B. talpa, male, lectotype, China, Shaanxi (coll. ZFMK); 2. B. talpa, female, paralectotype, China, Shaanxi (coll. ZFMK); 3. B. talpa, male, China, Sichuan (coll. AFM); 4. B. talpa, female, China, Sichuan (coll. NRCV); 7. B. antra sp. n., male, holotype, China, Sichuan (GBG / ZSM); 8. B. antra sp. n., female, paratype, China, Sichuan (AFM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224490/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
Figs 
<number box="[417,460,872,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
) [
<bibRefCitation author="Draudt" box="[482,963,871,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" refString="Draudt, M. (1950) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Agrotiden-Fauna Chinas aus den Ausbeuten Dr. H. Hone's. Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 40 (1), 1 - 174." type="journal article" year="1950">
Draudt, 
<number box="[577,637,871,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="1950.0">1950</number>
: 
<number box="[649,680,871,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="63.0">63</number>
; translated from 
<collectingCountry box="[870,963,872,896]" name="Germany" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">German</collectingCountry>
</bibRefCitation>
] 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[978,992,871,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">“</emphasis>
A small, delicate species. Head (
<figureCitation box="[1360,1428,871,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1764,1787]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,207,1731]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1744]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Maxiana gen. n., Euplexia spp., Bombyciella spp., adults, head and abdomen. 7. M. sericea, male, lectotype, China, Zhejiang (coll. ZFMK); 7 a. E. chloerythra, male, N. Vietnam, Lang Son (coll. NRCV); 8. M. sericea, males, lectotype and paralectotypes, China, Chekiang (coll. ZFMK); 9. B. talpa, male, lectotype, China, Shaanxi (coll. ZFMK); 10. M. sericea, male, China, Hunan (coll. ZFMK); 11. B. talpa, male, lectotype, China, Shaanxi (coll. ZFMK); 12. M. sericea, male, China, Hunan (coll. ZFMK)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224491/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
Fig. 
<number box="[1413,1428,872,896]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
) and thorax iron-black, tufts black, abdomen greyish-brown, tufts black. Forewings velvety mole-like grey, medial band coloured like thorax, bordered by deep-black transverse lines. Both these lines thinly bordered yellow at the far sides. The broad subbasal line black, between costa and submedian fold distally and posteriorly also thinly bordered yellow. Antemedian line curved back in cell, postmedial line slightly dentate, curving widely around the reniform stigma to reach the lower corner of the cell, continued in a shallow curve to hit the posterior margin almost at right angles. Both anterior stigmata large, lying in the somewhat lighter grey cell. Marginal area getting darker grey distally, a subterminal line shadowy indicated. Fringes of the same colour. 
<collectingCountry box="[1174,1230,1124,1149]" name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Hind</collectingCountry>
wings light grey, almost not darker at margin, underside even lighter, with a strong silken shine, discal dot, postmedial and subterminal line slightly indicated, almost invisible. Wingspan 
<quantity box="[859,978,1196,1221]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="24.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="22.0">22–26mm</quantity>
”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,486,1231,1256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Extended redescription</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[516,624,1231,1256]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1819,1842]" captionTargetBox="[164,1418,204,1783]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[156,1431,195,1795]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Bombyciella spp., adults. 1. B. talpa, male, lectotype, China, Shaanxi (coll. ZFMK); 2. B. talpa, female, paralectotype, China, Shaanxi (coll. ZFMK); 3. B. talpa, male, China, Sichuan (coll. AFM); 4. B. talpa, female, China, Sichuan (coll. NRCV); 7. B. antra sp. n., male, holotype, China, Sichuan (GBG / ZSM); 8. B. antra sp. n., female, paratype, China, Sichuan (AFM)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224490/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
Figs 
<number box="[581,624,1232,1256]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4</number>
</figureCitation>
) Wingspan of the available specimens 
<quantity box="[1113,1230,1231,1256]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="2.6" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="25.0" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="24.0">24–26mm</quantity>
, forewing length 
<quantity box="[151,263,1268,1292]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="11.0">11–12mm</quantity>
(N= 
<number box="[319,333,1268,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="5.0">5</number>
). Postmedial line of forewings always angled near posterior margin resulting in terminal part of the line reaching the posterior margin obliquely; upright scales of frons greyish-white. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1101,1281,1303,1328]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1296,1427,1303,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1781,1804]" captionTargetBox="[191,1406,199,1749]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[166,1420,193,1760]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Bombyciella spp. and Maxiana gen. n., male genitalia. 13. B. talpa, lectotype, gen. capsule, prep. 2269 - DS; 14. B. talpa, lectotype, aedeagus, prep. 2269 - DS; 15. B. antra sp. n., holotype, gen. capsule, prep. BJ 2160 m; 16. B. antra sp. n., holotype, aedeagus, prep. BJ 2160 m; 17. M. sericea, lectotype, gen. capsule, prep. 2270 - DS; 18. M. sericea, lectotype, aedeagus, prep. 2270 - DS;" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224492/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
) Uncus broad, dorso-ventrally flattened, rhombic shaped, weakly setose dorsally, apex acute; gnathus reduced; tegumen ventro-caudally with large, rounded peniculus lobes; vinculum large; saccus u-shaped; valvae broader at base, gradually tapering towards apex, apex evenly rounded, with distinct corona; cucullus weak; sacculus strongly sclerotized, harpe strong, S-curved and apically rounded and a rather large and strong, thorn-like, digitus present at ¾ of ventral margin of valvae; juxta with a large, spatulate process posteriorly; aedeagus strongly bent at caudal 
<number box="[1414,1425,1484,1508]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[151,167,1520,1544]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="3.0">3</number>
, carina present as a row of larger and smaller spines, vesica basally with a densely dentate surface and a group of narrow, rather long cornuti, arranged on a retroflexed diverticulum at middle. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1105,1316,1556,1581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1339,1427,1556,1581]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 22" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1764,1787]" captionTargetBox="[176,1405,193,1735]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[167,1419,193,1743]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 22. Maxiana gen. n., Bombyciella spp. and Euplexia spp. male and female genitalia. 19. M. sericea, paralectotype, gen. capsule, prep. 2272 - DS; 20. M. sericea, paralectotype, aedeagus, prep. 2272 - DS; 21. B. talpa, female, genitalia prep. BJ 2029 f; 22. B. antra sp. n., paratype female, genitalia prep. BJ 2030 f; 23. E. chloerythra, male, gen. capsule, prep. PGy 3913 m; 24. E. chloerythra, male, aedeagus, prep. PGy 3913 m." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224493/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
Fig. 
<number box="[1398,1427,1556,1580]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
) Ovipositor with elongated papillae anales; apophyses posteriores very long, apophyses anteriores short but thick, ostium bursae wide, sraightly-cutted, antrum strongly sclerotized and funnel-shaped; ductus rather long and gently curved, anteriorly tapering, cervix bursae small, conical in shape, corpus bursae membranous, narrow, sack-like, without signum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,530,1735,1760]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Bionomics and distribution.</emphasis>
The type-material and some additional specimens from the Höne collection have been collected at Taipai Shan the high point of Shaanxi Province, at elevations between 
<quantity box="[1135,1213,1772,1796]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" unit="m" value="1700.0">1700m</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[1267,1348,1772,1796]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" unit="m" value="3000.0">3000m</quantity>
, mainly in August. One specimen collected in May indicates a spring-generation in addition to this summer-generation. A single male and a few females collected at lights on very cold nights on 
<date box="[967,1166,1844,1869]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="1922-09-21">21, 22 September</date>
, 
<number box="[1178,1233,1844,1868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="2011.0">2011</number>
at an elevation of 
<quantity box="[151,307,1879,1904]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" unit="m" value="3400.0" valueMax="3500.0" valueMin="3300.0">3300–3500 m</quantity>
in shrubby, swampy areas of North and West Sichuan Province extend the known range of 
<taxonomicName box="[1346,1436,1879,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bombyciella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talpa">
<emphasis box="[1346,1436,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">B. talpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
considerably.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="553" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,2013]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1952,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">Etymology</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Draudt" box="[342,549,1952,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" refString="Draudt, M. (1950) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Agrotiden-Fauna Chinas aus den Ausbeuten Dr. H. Hone's. Mitteilungen der Munchner Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 40 (1), 1 - 174." type="journal article" year="1950">
Draudt (
<number box="[438,499,1952,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="1950.0">1950</number>
: 
<number box="[512,541,1952,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" value="63.0">63</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described the ground colour of this species as “velvety mole-like grey”. The species-name “ 
<taxonomicName box="[319,377,1988,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bombyciella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talpa">talpa</taxonomicName>
” is derived from the generic name of the European Mole, 
<emphasis box="[1030,1205,1988,2013]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="553">
<taxonomicName box="[1030,1093,1988,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Bombyciella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="559" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="talpa">Talpa</taxonomicName>
europaea
</emphasis>
Linnaeus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
